comments.body: [~accountid:63113ce88473817d7d04b3d3] [~accountid:5b5631f96366b42ca0ded60d] [~accountid:613e6eaa1238e8007108f513] we are unable to delete this profile (DUPE51) [https://app.ganaz.com/o/0/company/60/hiring/754330|https://app.ganaz.com/o/0/company/60/hiring/754330] as it has an active paycard attached.

Thank you for the heads up, [~accountid:62780ad493111000689ece08] , Tiffany did say they were going to issue a paycard to this worker today—so I see they assigned it to one of the Dupe profiles 🤦

I am thinking, could we move the completed hiring info into DUPE51 instead? Then we can remove 51 and then after that I’ll just rename DUPE51 to just 51. Thoughts?

Generally, we don’t move hiring documents.



But we can move a paycard to the “correct” profile and drop the old profile. (Dan, this means modifying the cardholder_to_person table _and_ modifying packet_instance so that we maintain the historical record of the person signing the cardholder docs)

[~accountid:63113ce88473817d7d04b3d3] [~accountid:5b5631f96366b42ca0ded60d] ok this is completed, the active paycard has been moved to [https://app.ganaz.com/o/0/company/60/hiring/754335|https://app.ganaz.com/o/0/company/60/hiring/754335] and the two duplicated person records have been deleted.
Fantastic, Thank you all so much!!!

fields.customfield_10131: Customer is currently hiring new employees so if this could be completed at your earliest convenience that would be greatly appreciated!

comments.body: [~accountid:63113ce88473817d7d04b3d3]  there’s an id {{TEST 0005}} also. Should that stay or be removed?
I want to understand what’s involved when deleting a CH before completing this ticket.
we don't have a process for this today, but general guidance is we can't ever delete a real cardholder. Kyle is looking into how we should proceed for cases like this.

No transactions are found for Nubia Ramos. 
We have discussed how to do this going forward and our process will be documented in confluence. 

*if it is truly a test CH, must be verified in qolo*
person entry will be deleted
cardholder_to_person will be deleted (audit trail)
cardholder will never be deleted

if it is NOT a test CH then case-by-case verification. 
Special care absolutely if there’s money on the account. That must be approved by Emma/Kyle before we do anything.

Hello [~accountid:613e6eaa1238e8007108f513] & [~accountid:62780ad493111000689ece08], Thank you so much for confirming!
Test 0005 we are keeping on there so that we can run tests/preview packets in the future! We’ve begun leaving 1 Test profile in each account now so that in the future if the customer wishes to preview packets they can use the “+New Document” workflow within the test profile’s hiring page. 

Regarding Nubia, I didn’t realize she had issued herself a card! If she did do so, we should definitely leave it there—she is one of our POCs at the farm so she may have decided to test this—but it is better to leave it there then remove it 👍 

If she reaches back out wishing it to be removed we can take additional steps at that time.

[~accountid:63113ce88473817d7d04b3d3]  I did not see your message until now. Nubia Ramos is deleted as a person and she’s also deleted from the cardholder_to_person table. 

We never delete from the cardholder table. The card doesn’t have any funds and never had any funds and after this deletion I don’t think the card should be used.

Hi Kjell, No worries—I will let Nubia know! If it didn’t have funds on it then it was likely only meant to be a test. I will let them know if they wish to have Nubia test it out then they can rehire/reissue if needed 🙌 

Thank you again for all of your help!
